Class FramePosition

java.lang.Object
  sim.FramePosition

public abstract class FramePosition
extends java.lang.Object

FramePosition is an abstract class which provides some useful functions for positioning JFrames on the screen.

positionFrame

public static void positionFrame(javax.swing.JFrame frame,
                                 int position)
Positions a JFrame on the screen using the specified integer position value, e.g. FramePosition.NORTH_WEST, FramePosition.NORTH_EAST etc.

Parameters:
frame - the JFrame to be position on the screen.
position - an integer value.

positionFrame

public static void positionFrame(javax.swing.JFrame frame1,
                                 int position,
                                 javax.swing.JFrame frame2)
Positions the given JFrame on the screen relative to another JFrame, using the specified integer position value, e.g. FramePosition.NORTH_WEST, FramePosition.CENTER etc.

Parameters:
frame1 - the JFrame to be positioned on the screen.
position - an integer value.
frame2 - the other JFrame to which frame1 is aligned.
